'''Very.co.uk''' is a British online retailer with headquarters in [[Speke]], [[Liverpool]]. The brand was launched in the UK in July 2009 as part of [[Shop Direct Group]]. Very had formerly been known as [[Littlewoods|Littlewoods Direct]].

=== History ===

The original Littlewoods brand was a shopping catalogue and retail business headquartered in Liverpool, and was bought by the [[Barclay brothers]] in 2002.<ref>{{cite news|last=Hodgson|first=Neil|title=Famous name on way out|url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/liverpool-news/famous-name-on-way-out-3485571|accessdate=17 March 2014|date=8 May 2008}}</ref> In 2009, Littlewoods Direct was rebranded as Very.co.uk, shifting its focus to online retailing and a younger market.<ref name="RW rebrand">{{cite news|last=Danaher|first=Tim|title=Littlewoods Direct to undergo Very rebrand|url=http://www.retail-week.com/multichannel/littlewoods-direct-to-undergo-very-rebrand/5003658.article|accessdate=17 March 2014|newspaper=Retail Week|date=19 June 2009}}</ref><ref name="MW rebrand">{{cite news|last=Ramsay|first=Fiona|title=Shop Direct tasks VCCP with rebranding Littlewoods Direct|url=http://www.marketingmagazine.co.uk/article/916399/shop-direct-tasks-vccp-rebranding-littlewoods-direct-verycouk|accessdate=17 March 2014|newspaper=Marketing Week|date=29 June 2009}}</ref>
The Very.co.uk website launched officially in July 2009. A year later a mobile enabled version of the site site was launched, upgrading to include video and images in 2011.<ref name="Internet Retailing">{{cite news|last=Alison|title=Fashion site Very.co.uk upgrades to deliver rich media on mobile devices|url=http://internetretailing.net/2011/02/fashion-site-very-co-uk-upgrades-to-deliver-rich-media-on-mobile-devices/|accessdate=17 March 2014|newspaper=Internet Retailing|date=22 February 2011}}</ref> In the first quarter of 2013/14, mobile sales accounted for over a third of total online sales.<ref name=Reuters>{{cite news|last=Davey|first=James|title=Shop Direct makes first profit in a decade|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2013/10/29/uk-shop-direct-results-idUKBRE99S0AU20131029|accessdate=17 March 2014|date=29 October 2013}}</ref>
=== Partnerships and promotion ===

Very.co.uk makes extensive use of both celebrity endorsements and product placement on television and other media. [[Holly Willoughby]] and [[Fearne Cotton]] have acted as faces of the site, creating branded fashion collections and appearing in adverts.<ref name=Reuters>{{cite news|last=Davey|first=James|title=Shop Direct makes first profit in a decade|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2013/10/29/uk-shop-direct-results-idUKBRE99S0AU20131029|accessdate=17 March 2014|date=29 October 2013}}</ref><ref name="Guardian ad">{{cite news|last=Creative Lounge Index|title=Watch Holly Willougby and Fearne Cotton in a festive ad for Very.co.uk|url=http://www.theguardian.com/media/video/2009/oct/29/holly-willougby-fearne-cotton-ad|accessdate=17 March 2014|newspaper=The Guardian|date=30 October 2009}}</ref> Other names who have worked with the brand include [[Jameela Jamil]] and [[Diana Vickers]].<ref name=Company>{{cite news|title=Jameela Jamil Launches Fashion Collection|url=http://www.company.co.uk/fashion/news/jameela-jamil-fashion-collection|accessdate=17 March 2014|newspaper=Company}}</ref><ref name="DM Jamil">{{cite news|last=Hardingham-Gill|first=Tamara|title=Hats off to her! Jameela Jamil unveils latest collection for Very.co.uk in Mad Hatter style shoot|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2198273/Hats-Jameela-Jamil-unveils-latest-collection-Very-uk-Mad-Hatter-style-shoot.html|accessdate=17 March 2014|newspaper=Daily Mail|date=7 September 2012}}</ref><ref name="DM Vickers">{{cite news|last=Paxman|first=Lauren|title=Diana Vickers puts THAT advert behind her for second collection for Very|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2087954/Diana-Vickers-puts-THAT-advert-second-collection-Very-uk.html|accessdate=17 March 2014|newspaper=Daily Mail|date=18 January 2012}}</ref> In December 2013, former [[Girls Aloud]] member [[Kimberley Walsh]] became a celebrity designer for Very.<ref name="IS Walsh">{{cite news|last=Martin|first=Rebecca|title=Kimberley Walsh Launches Her Debut Range For Very.co.uk... And It's Totally Gorgeous|url=http://www.instyle.co.uk/fashion/news/kimberley-walsh-launches-her-debut-range-for-verycouk-and-its-totally-gorgeous|accessdate=17 March 2014|newspaper=In Style|date=21 January 2014}}</ref>
Very has sponsored [[V Festival|V music festival]], also offering a delivery service to the festival sites in 2012.<ref name="Drum V Festival">{{cite news|last=West|first=Gillian|title=Very.co.uk to deliver direct to this year's V Festival|url=http://www.thedrum.com/news/2012/07/19/verycouk-deliver-direct-years-v-festival|accessdate=17 March 2014|newspaper=The Drum|date=19 July 2012}}</ref> It has also sponsored [[Celebrity Big Brother]] on Channel 5, with branded, 'click-to-buy' product placement.<ref name="Big Brother MW">{{cite news|last=Farey-Jones|first=Daniel|title=Very.co.uk strikes click-to-buy partnership with Channel 5|url=http://www.mediaweek.co.uk/article/1165415/verycouk-strikes-click-to-buy-partnership-channel-5|accessdate=17 March 2014|newspaper=Media Week|date=3 January 2013}}</ref><ref name="The Drum">{{cite news|last=Macleod|first=Ishbel|title=Channel 5 and Very.co.uk unveil 360 click-to-buy product placement initiative in Big Brother|url=http://www.thedrum.com/news/2013/06/13/channel-5-and-verycouk-unveil-360-click-buy-product-placement-initiative-big-brother|accessdate=17 March 2014|date=13 June 2013}}</ref>
